  "narrative_arc": "Given away as a child bride, brutalized by her husband, separated from her sister. Celie's transformation comes through love (Shug), creativity (pants-making), and literacy (letters). Walker documents every dimension of Southern Black women's oppression and then maps every dimension of liberation — all without any formal system intervening.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Celie's dome is defined by the absence of systems and the presence of community. Layer 2 (Systems) is empty — no government helped her. Layer 8 (Community), Layer 11 (Creativity), and Layer 12 (Flourishing) are what saved her. Her dome proves that human layers can compensate for empty institutional layers.",
